        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 3:39PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 339 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles northeast of Hysham, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vananda.
</description>
        <instruction>Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm. Do not drive your
vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
